Category 	Video Files
File Description 	High definition video file saved in the MPEG-2 Part 1 transport format; used for multiplexing digital video and audio streams and synchronizing the output; includes features for error correction and is often used in digital video broadcasting (DVB).

TRP files often contain H.264 video and AC3 audio data; they can be played with various video playback programs.

Video transport themes may also be saved as .TS files.
